<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> ball is in someone’s court, the • have the ball at one’s feet</xh5><p> <i>ball is in someone’s court, the</i>—is used to say that another person must make the next move: Addison tells him that <u>the ball is in his court</u>. All he has to do is sign the divorce papers and she will too.</p><p> <i>have the ball at one’s feet—</i>be in a strategically advantageous position: The working class militants <u>have the ball at their feet</u>, as never before.</p> </entry>
